            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "## Autovacuum Blockers & Wraparound Identification\r\n\r\n\r\n<h6>*In this workbook we will try to identify blockers preventing autovacuum from removing dead tuples and fixes to mitigate the issue.The workbook also gives details if the databases on the server are closer to triggering emergency autovaccum  or if the databases are closer to transactionID wraparound problem. *</h6>\r\n\r\nStep | Observations\r\n--- | ---\r\n**Emergency Autovaccum and Transaction ID Wraparound Issue Identification** | Step 1: Analyze the metric to understand how close the databases on the server are to trigger a emergency autovaccum or transaction ID wraparound protection. The section also provides resolutions around it.\r\n**Autovaccum Blockers** | Step 2: Workbook would identify if any autovacuum blockers - long running transactions, inactive replication slots or orphaned prepared transactions exist on the server and shares the blocker details along with mitigation steps. If there are no blockers then autovacuum blockers section would indicate no blockers found.\r\n\r\n"
            },
            "name": "text - 0"
          }
        ],
        "exportParameters": true
      },
      "name": "WorkbookTop"
    },
